---
import Layout from "../layouts/layouts.astro";
import MapEmbed from "../components/MapEmbed.astro";
---

<Layout title="Beaches, Pools & Water Activities">
	<h1>Beaches, Pools &amp; Water Activities</h1>

	<section class="heroCard">
	<div class="introGrid">
		<p>
			Cooling down on very hot days is often needed. These are our go-to spots around Lake Trasimeno and nearby.
		Waterparks in rural Italy are more relaxed than in Spain / Portugal and are often where local families get together / celebrate birthdays.
		A good option if travelling with or without kids. Use the map at the bottom to see locations, notes, and any extra details.
	</p>

		<img
			src="/photos/lake-trasimeno.jpg"
			alt="Lake Trasimeno"
			loading="lazy"
		/>
	</div>
</section>
	

	<h2>Beaches &amp; Pools</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Castiglione Beach, Bed &amp; Kayak Rental</strong><br />
			Shallow entry and safe for kids. Small sandy stretch (lake bottom can be muddy/silty). Sunbeds available, plus pedalo/kayak rental.
			Drop into Pescatore Cafe nearby for a coffee or drink for the full “beach day” vibe.
		</li>

		<li>
			<strong>Alternative Castiglione Beach</strong><br />
			Another easy shallow-entry option near town with a small sandy stretch and a relaxed lakeside feel.
		</li>

		<li>
			<strong>Kitemaniak – Kitesurfing &amp; SUP</strong><br />
			Local kitesurfing and SUP school—good if you want something more active on the lake.
		</li>

		<li>
			<strong>Spiaggia di Punta Navaccia (Tuoro)</strong><br />
			An alternative lakeside stop with a different view and closer to the islands. A little run down, but fine for a visit.
		</li>

		<li>
			<strong>Sualzo Beach &amp; Pool</strong><br />
			A nice pool with a great lake view—ideal if you’re on the north side of the lake (Cortona / Passignano area).
			Darker sand on the beach and some kayak/SUP rental options nearby. Easy to pair with Passignano’s lakefront cafés.
		</li>

		<li>
			<strong>Piscina Comunale di Chianciano Terme (Outdoor pools &amp; diving)</strong> —
			<a href="http://www.virtusbuonconvento.it/chianciano-terme.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">website</a><br />
			Big outdoor municipal swimming pool with a local feel. Great for serious swimmers/divers, plus a kids pool—handy after exploring the Tuscan countryside.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Waterparks</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Laguna Park (Waterpark)</strong> —
			<a href="http://www.lagunaparktrasimeno.it/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">website</a><br />
			Spotlessly clean, family-friendly waterpark. Slides for kids, big grass area, football/volleyball, bar and restaurant.
			A great “very hot day” option.
		</li>

		<li>
			<strong>Oasi del Tezio Acquapark (Colle Umberto)</strong> —
			<a href="https://oasideltezio.it/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">website</a><br />
			Nice waterpark with a good local vibe. Decent slides for families (including one suitable for older kids), plus a good bar, small playground and volleyball courts.
		</li>

		<li>
			<strong>Tavernelle Aquatic Park</strong> —
			<a href="http://www.azzurrapiscine.it/aquapark-tavernelle/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">website</a><br />
			Good mix of slides and diving boards for younger and older kids. Bar/snacks onsite. Nice to pair with sunset drinks in Panicale on the way home.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<h2>Map</h2>
	<p style="color: var(--muted); margin-top: -6px;">
		Tip: click pinned items on the map for extra detail.
	</p>
	<MapEmbed
		title="Pools & Water Activities"
		src="https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=1a2oM7W-xnqOsIZRi-pOtbrEa2Mw4N6k&ehbc=2E312F"
	/>

	<style>
		ul { padding-left: 20px; }
		li { margin: 10px 0; }
	
.heroCard {
	background: var(--card);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: var(--radius);
	padding: 16px;
	margin: 12px 0 18px;
}

.introGrid {
	display: grid;
	gap: 16px;
	align-items: start;
}

.introGrid p {
	margin: 0;
	color: var(--text);
	font-size: 16px;
	line-height: 1.6;
}

.introGrid img {
	width: 100%;
	height: 260px;          /* makes it look intentional */
	object-fit: cover;      /* prevents awkward stretching */
	display: block;
	border-radius: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
}

@media (min-width: 860px) {
	.introGrid {
		grid-template-columns: 1.25fr 0.75fr;
		align-items: center; /* vertically aligns text + image */
	}
	.introGrid img {
		height: 240px;
	}
}

ul { padding-left: 20px; }
li { margin: 12px 0; }
li br { display: block; margin: 6px 0 0; }

    </style>
</Layout>